title: How many Elon-backed challengers will win seats in Congress in 2026?
rules_primary: If Elon Musk supports at least 5 non-incumbents who win Congressional seats in 2026, then the market resolves to Yes.
info_risk_rationale: The 2026 House/Senate outcome is still many months away and requires five separate non-incumbent wins, so short-term signals (single endorsements, rumors, or small polls) over the next 7 days are unlikely to shift the aggregated probability by more than 20%. Elon Musk can produce sudden headlines, but such events in a one-week window are uncommon and would more likely move sentiment for individual races than change the market’s estimate of achieving five+ wins, so I assess a low (~15%) chance of a >20% price move in the next 7 days.
fair_value_rationale: Musk has the funding and organizational reach to back multiple Congressional challengers (via America PAC and large 2024 donations), but his slate-level track record is mixed and some recent, high-profile picks have lost. ([en.wikipedia.org](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/America_PAC?utm_source=openai)) Historical midterm patterns and local dynamics mean many non-incumbents do win in a cycle, so if Musk backs a sizable, well-targeted slate he could clear five wins — but uncertainty about how many viable challengers he will endorse and how voters respond makes a successful five-plus outcome only moderately likely. ([news.gallup.com](https://news.gallup.com/poll/242093/midterm-seat-loss-averages-unpopular-presidents.aspx?utm_source=openai))
early_close_condition: This market will close and expire early if the event occurs.
rules_secondary: Special elections between Jun 4, 2025 and election day 2026 are also included in this number.

title: Will Gonzaga be the West Coast Conference regular season champions?
rules_primary: If Gonzaga is the 2025-26 Men's College Basketball West Coast Conference regular season champion, then the market resolves to Yes.
info_risk_rationale: Gonzaga opens WCC play on Dec 28, 2025 and is the preseason favorite with recent coverage highlighting healthy key players and no major injury reports. ([slipperstillfits.com](https://www.slipperstillfits.com/news/24704/gonzagas-braden-huff-wins-second-wcc-player-of-the-week-award?utm_source=openai)) Given that only an early conference game or routine team news is likely in the next 7 days, the odds of a rare, market-moving event (major injury, suspension, or shocking upset) large enough to swing the price >20% are low but non-negligible—hence ~15%.
fair_value_rationale: Gonzaga was the clear preseason favorite in the WCC coaches’ poll (nine first-place votes), which reflects coaches’ expectations and Gonzaga’s program strength. ([wccsports.com](https://wccsports.com/news/2025/10/18/athlete-awards-gonzaga-picked-to-win-2025-26-west-coast-conference-mens-basketball-championship.aspx?utm_source=openai)) Gonzaga also enters the season nationally ranked with a strong non-conference record and impact players (e.g., Braden Huff, Graham Ike), which makes them a likely regular-season leader. ([slipperstillfits.com](https://www.slipperstillfits.com/news/24702/gonzaga-stays-put-in-ap-poll?utm_source=openai)) That said, Saint Mary’s — the 2024–25 regular-season champion — remains a proven challenger, which prevents a higher probability. ([wccsports.com](https://wccsports.com/news/2025/2/25/athlete-awards-wcc-announces-2024-25-mens-basketball-all-conference-awards.aspx?utm_source=openai))
early_close_condition: This market will close and expire early after a result is declared.
rules_secondary: If multiple participants are officially recognized as co-champions, then the markets for those participants will resolve such that “Yes” holders receive $1 / [number of co-champions]

title: Will Elon Musk be the world's first trillionaire?
rules_primary: If Elon Musk is the world's first trillionare before Jan 1, 2030 then the market resolves to Yes.
info_risk_rationale: There are no scheduled, definitive corporate events (Tesla earnings and no announced SpaceX IPO or similar liquidity event) in the Dec 26, 2025–Jan 2, 2026 window and publicly reported estimates place Musk’s net worth well below $1 trillion today, so a >20‑point move from 88% in a single week is unlikely. ([investing.com](https://www.investing.com/equities/tesla-motors-earnings?utm_source=openai)) However, private tender transactions, a surprise SpaceX valuation/IPO announcement, a very large Tesla shock, or an unexpected legal/health development could still produce a rapid sentiment swing, so I assign a small non‑zero chance (~7%). ([ebc.com](https://www.ebc.com/forex/spacex-ipo-in-2026-valuation-date-and-how-to-invest?utm_source=openai))
fair_value_rationale: Musk already has an estimated net worth in the roughly $700–750B range and controls very large stakes in Tesla (market cap ≈ $1.6T) and SpaceX (private valuations reported near $800B), plus a potentially huge Tesla pay package — a combination of continued equity upside, a SpaceX IPO or insider liquidity could push him over $1T before 1 Jan 2030. However, meaningful risks (market crashes, regulatory/legal setbacks, dilution or failure to realize pay-package value) make the outcome far from certain, so I assign a modestly better-than-even probability. ([reuters.com](https://www.reuters.com/business/autos-transportation/elon-musk-becomes-first-person-worth-700-billion-after-court-ruling-pay-package-2025-12-20/?utm_source=openai))
early_close_condition: This market will close and expire early if an individual becomes a trillionairel.

title: Will any performer sing DÁKITI at the Super Bowl?
rules_primary: If any performer sings DÁKITI at the 2026 Super Bowl, then the market resolves to Yes.
info_risk_rationale: Bad Bunny has already been announced as the Super Bowl LX headliner and “DÁKITI” is one of his signature hits, so the market has largely priced in a high chance that the song could appear. A genuinely market-moving announcement in the next seven days (explicit setlist confirmation, major guest reveal, or an unexpected cancellation) could shift prices >20%, but concrete setlist confirmations this far out are uncommon and such shocks are unlikely in the next week. ([cbssports.com](https://www.cbssports.com/nfl/news/bad-bunny-selected-to-perform-during-2026-super-bowl-lx-halftime-show/?utm_source=openai))
fair_value_rationale: Bad Bunny has been announced as the headliner for the Super Bowl LX halftime show (Feb 8, 2026), and the halftime set is typically a short medley of an artist’s biggest hits. "Dákiti" is one of Bad Bunny’s signature, globally streamed songs, so it is highly likely he (or a guest during his set) will perform at least part of it during the halftime show. ([ew.com](https://ew.com/fat-joe-honors-mega-star-bad-bunny-entertainers-of-the-year-11874752))
early_close_condition: This market will close and expire early if the event occurs.

title: Will Donald Trump announce a run for President of the United States before Jan 1, 2027?
rules_primary: If Donald Trump has announced that they will run for President of the United States in 2028 before Jan 1, 2027, including running for the nomination of any political party to contest that office, then the market resolves to Yes.
info_risk_rationale: Very unlikely — President Trump has publicly acknowledged the constitutional limit on a third elected term and multiple major outlets report he has said he’s “not allowed to run,” making a formal 2028 campaign announcement in the next 7 days improbable. There are no credible reports of a scheduled announcement or imminent campaign filing, so the chance of market-moving news between Dec 26, 2025 and Jan 1, 2026 is small (~3%). ([washingtonpost.com](https://www.washingtonpost.com/politics/2025/10/28/mike-johnson-trump-third-term/?utm_source=openai))
fair_value_rationale: As of Dec 26, 2025 Donald Trump is serving a second term and is constrained by the 22nd Amendment, so a formal announcement that he will run in 2028 before Jan 1, 2027 is unlikely given constitutional and political realities. ([cnbc.com](https://www.cnbc.com/2025/03/30/trump-wont-rule-out-seeking-a-third-term-in-the-white-house.html?utm_source=openai)) He has repeatedly teased a third-term bid and allies (e.g., Steve Bannon) continue to promote ways around term limits, so there remains a nonzero chance he publicly declares an intent to run, but legal hurdles and political incentives make that outcome improbable. ([newsmax.com](https://www.newsmax.com/politics/steven-bannon-donald-trump-third-term/2025/10/24/id/1231725/?utm_source=openai))
early_close_condition: This market will close and expire early if the person announces their candidacy.
rules_secondary: The person must publicly announce their campaign for it to be reported by a Source Agency. Merely filing campaign paperwork with the Federal Election Commission or similar entity is insufficient without a public announcement. The announcement must be for the specific office and election year listed. Exploratory committees or statements of interest without formal campaign announcements do not qualify. Running for a party's nomination to contest the office counts as running for that office. The announcement must come from the person themselves or their official campaign, not from speculation or third-party sources.

title: Who will run for the Republican presidential nomination in 2028?
rules_primary: If Ron DeSantis announces a presidential campaign to contest the presidential nomination of the Republican party for the 2028 U.S. presidential election, then the market resolves to Yes.
info_risk_rationale: Low — there are no credible reports or a scheduled announcement indicating DeSantis will declare a 2028 presidential campaign in the next seven days; recent coverage shows him focused on Florida governance and policy actions rather than a national launch. A surprise campaign announcement (which would likely push the market well above +20%) or an explicit public withdrawal (which would push it well below −20%) are the main news types that could move the price materially, and neither appears likely during this holiday week absent an unexpected decision. ([apnews.com](https://apnews.com/article/7d8fdf8be199304688db1726130e3df2?utm_source=openai))
fair_value_rationale: I assign about a 60% chance because DeSantis remains a widely discussed, plausible 2028 contender — he is term‑limited as Florida governor after 2026 and has been repeatedly mentioned in media analyses as a possible return to the presidential stage, even though he had not publicly launched a 2028 campaign as of Dec 26, 2025.  His national standing was weakened by the 2024 withdrawal and current polling places him behind some other GOP figures, but his name recognition, donor/network infrastructure, and ongoing media speculation make an official announcement fairly likely. ([apnews.com](https://apnews.com/article/250c8ed4b49843350e258f0c2754c8ba?utm_source=openai))
early_close_condition: This market will close and expire early if the event occurs.
